This paper deals with a logical system that involves modalities and quantification, which are typical topics in the subfield of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the undecidability of the satisfiability problem, which is a common theme in the subfield of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of arrow updates suggests a connection to programming languages and semantics (cs.PL), while the dynamic nature of the logic may relate to natural language processing and discourse analysis (cs.CL). Finally, the reduction of the tiling problem involves combinatorial and algorithmic aspects, which are relevant to the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
